NEW Africa Cup of Nations, Senegal recieved a hero’s welcome when they returned to the capital Dakar from Egypt. Thousands of fans descended at the Léopold Sédar Senghor International Airport on Monday to welcome and celebrate with their heros'.  President o the country Macky Sall was also at the airport to welcome the team that overcame Egypt 4-2 in a penalty shoot-out in Sunday’s final in Cameroon’s capital Yaounde. Their achievement has brought smiles to the faces of thousands of Senegalese fans, with President Sall declaring Monday a public holiday so that celebrations could continue. Here's how they welcomed them.  Champions d’Afrique !!! Quel match! Quelle équipe ! Vous l’avez fait! Beau moment de football, beau moment de communion et de fierté nationale.Tellement fiers de vous! Félicitations à nos héros ! Coupe bi nieuw na!????MERCI JËRËJËF pic.twitter.com/9tZZbJlj4P 